'''Haidar el Ali''' is a [[Senegal]]ese ecologist, appointed Minister of Ecology in April 2012.<ref>[https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/senegal/9187892/Senegal-musician-Youssou-Ndour-appointed-culture-minister.html "Senegal musician Youssou Ndour appointed culture minister"], in The Telegraph, 5 Apr 2012</ref> In 2013 he became the Minister of Fisheries.<ref>[http://www.gouv.sn/Decret-no-2013-1223-du-02.html Décret n° 2013-1223 du 02 septembre 2013 portant composition du Gouvernement], retrieved 8 August 2015</ref><ref>Alex Duval Smith: [https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2014/feb/26/senegal-fisheries-minister-foreign-factory-ships "Senegal's firebrand fisheries minister turns his ire on foreign factory ships "], in ''[[The Guardian]]'', 26 February 2014</ref> He is also president of the [[Senegalese Green Party]] (FEDES).<ref>[http://europeangreens.eu/fr/node/6103 Haidar El Ali, leader of the Senegalese Green Party, FEDES, is the country's destruction minister], 5 April 2012</ref>
