{{unreliable sources|date=July 2012}} {{Use mdy dates|date=October 2011}} '''Jamie Drummond''' (born November 7, 1971) is a Canadian [[sommelier]], wine consultant, and writer who acts as Senior Editor and Director of Programs for Toronto not-for-profit Good Food Revolution.<ref name="tlife">{{cite web |last=Aronovitch |first=Davida |url=http://www.torontolife.com/daily/daily-dish/rumours-rumblings/2009/09/21/closing-in-on-the-sale-of-the-jamie-kennedy-wine-bar/ |title=Closing in on the sale of the Jamie Kennedy Wine Bar &#124; Rumours & Rumblings |publisher=torontolife.com |date=September 21, 2009 |accessdate=October 18, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120227035038/http://www.torontolife.com/daily/daily-dish/rumours-rumblings/2009/09/21/closing-in-on-the-sale-of-the-jamie-kennedy-wine-bar/ |archive-date=February 27, 2012 |dead-url=yes |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Drummond was born in [[Edinburgh]], Scotland, and is a former pupil of [[George Watson's College]].<ref>[http://www.gwc.org.uk/WatsoniansDonors/reunions/current/nextReunion.php?year=1989 ]{{dead link|date=October 2011}}</ref> Following this Drummond went on to read [[Cultural Studies]] at the [[University of East London]], UK.{{Citation needed|date=November 2009}}
Drummond began working as a sommelier for UK Chef Andrew Radford's [[Michelin Guide]] recognised Atrium restaurant in [[Edinburgh]], Scotland.<ref>{{cite web|author=Photo by Chloé Dulude |url=http://enroute.aircanada.com/en/articles/spin-the-bottle |title=enRoute &#124; Spin the Bottle |publisher=Enroute.aircanada.com |date=March 1, 2009 |accessdate=October 18, 2011}}</ref><ref name="tasteto.com">[http://www.tasteto.com/2007/06/21/tasting-to-with-jamie-drummond/ ] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070929035646/http://www.tasteto.com/2007/06/21/tasting-to-with-jamie-drummond/ |date=September 29, 2007 }}</ref> During this time he studied with the United Kingdom's [[Wine & Spirit Education Trust]] (WSET).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sommelierservice.com/show_info.php?page_id=7&osCsid=cb0661d386cf22474e8e4c98de31c588 |title=Sommelier Service |publisher=Sommelier Service |accessdate=October 18, 2011}}</ref><ref name="royalfair.org">{{cite web |url=http://www.royalfair.org/files/Wine%20Competition%20Judges%20List.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-11-30 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101129212023/http://royalfair.org/files/Wine%20Competition%20Judges%20List.pdf |archivedate=November 29, 2010 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> In 1997 Drummond emigrated to Canada and began working as Sommelier at Toronto's [[Granite Club]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.torontolife.com/features/nose-job/ |title=Nose Job |publisher=torontolife.com |date=March 30, 2011 |accessdate=October 18, 2011 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110927153550/http://www.torontolife.com/features/nose-job/ |archive-date=September 27, 2011 |dead-url=yes |df=mdy-all }}</ref> In 2004 he was hired by [[Jamie Kennedy (chef)|Jamie Kennedy]] and was in control of the selection and purchasing of wines for Kennedy's restaurants<ref>[https://nationalpost.com/life/story.html?id=552759 ]{{dead link|date=October 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.citybites.ca/archives/CityBites_Nov08.pdf |title=CityBItes TEMP (Page 1) |format=PDF |accessdate=October 18, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111008032126/http://www.citybites.ca/archives/CityBites_Nov08.pdf |archivedate=October 8, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> until late 2009.<ref name="tlife"/> For some time it was rumoured that he was the chef behind [[Charlie's Burgers]] in Toronto,<ref>{{cite web|author=Susan Sampson Food Writer |url=https://www.thestar.com/living/article/608942 |title=Delicious, mysterious, covert cuisine |work=Toronto Star |date=March 27, 2009 |accessdate=October 18, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www2.macleans.ca/tag/charlies-burgers/ |title=Charlie’s Burgers – Topics |publisher=Macleans.ca |date=March 30, 2009 |accessdate=October 18, 2011}}</ref> which was not the case.<ref>{{cite web|author=james chatto |url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/life/food-and-wine/trends/trends-features/revealed-charlie-burgers-true-identity/article2107039/ |title=Revealed: Charlie Burger's true identity |work=Globe and Mail |location=Canada |accessdate=October 18, 2011}}</ref> Drummond has served as a wine judge for Intervin, BioVino, Ontario Wine Awards, Royal Agricultural Winter Fair.<ref name="royalfair.org"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.intervin.ca/sitepages/?cid=323&cn=MEET%20THE%20JUDGES&an=MEET%20THE%20JUDGES |title=Intervin |publisher=Intervin.ca |accessdate=October 18, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tastecelebration.ca/judges.html |title=Taste! A Celebration of Regional Cuisine – Prince Edward County, Ontario |publisher=Tastecelebration.ca |date=June 28, 2008 |accessdate=October 18, 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110828104708/http://www.tastecelebration.ca/judges.html |archivedate=August 28, 2011 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> He also occasionally DJ's in Toronto as DJ Non Doctor.<ref name="tasteto.com"/><ref>{{cite web|author=Signe Langford Special to the Star |url=https://www.thestar.com/living/wine/article/834842--wine-women-and-the-glass-ceiling |title=Wine, women and the glass ceiling |work=Toronto Star |date=July 20, 2010 |accessdate=October 18, 2011}}</ref>
