{{expand language|topic=|langcode=zh|otherarticle=屯門色魔|date=September 2012}} {{Infobox serial killer | name=Lam Kwok-wai | image= | caption= | birth_name= | alias=The Tuen Mun Rapist | birth_date={{birth date and age|df=yes|1971|1|27}} | birth_place=[[Hong Kong]] | death_date= | cause= | victims=3 murders | country= | states= | apprehended={{date|August 9th 1993}} | penalty=[[Life imprisonment]] }}
'''Lam Kwok-wai''' (born 27 January 1971) is one of [[Hong Kong]]'s two known [[serial killer]]s.
He was convicted of 10 rapes and three murders. His murder weapon was his bare hands; he referred to his right hand as his "fork".
== Victims (murders only)== *Li Hing, female, age 50, body found in the [[Yau Oi Estate]] [[Tuen Mun]] *Mak Siu-han, female. age 22, body found in [[Tai Hing Estate|Hing Shing House]] [[Tuen Mun]] *Lau Siu-man, female, age 23, body found in [[Hung Hom]]
== Popular culture == *Lam Kwok-wai is portrayed in the movie ''Tuen Mun sik mo (The Rapist)'' (1994).<ref>https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0111515/</ref>
