'''William Clingan''' (c.1721 &ndash; May 9, 1790) was a delegate in the [[Continental Congress]] for [[Pennsylvania]] from 1777 to 1779. He signed the [[Articles of Confederation]]. Upon his death he was buried in the Upper Octorara Church Cemetery in [[Parkesburg, Pennsylvania]].<ref>{{Find a Grave|6860272}}</ref> William Clingan and his brother immigrated to the Colonies from Scotland. His last name, Clingan, came from the Scottish surname of MacClingan. Much regarding his life is unknown.

